Facial Emotional Recognition (FER)
The work of Dr. Hauschild deals with the ability of infants, neurotypical, and neurodivergent individuals and how well they process emotional features of faces and voices.

Name: Dr. Kate Hauschild
Degree: PhD, Developmental Cognitive Psychology
Research Interests: 

1) explore the connection between early cognitive and social communication deficits associated with ASD, 2) examine how these deficits may have cascading effects on social functioning and interaction later in life, and 3) apply this knowledge to the development and implementation of early intervention programs.
